<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-11-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-11-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="10" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d10">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Buchanan</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos
                                        Ayres</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-11-16"><hi rend="italic">November 16,
                                    1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Hawaiian schooner <hi rend="italic">Americana</hi>, carrying the flag of
                            Hawaii, has arrived from St. John, where was cleared by consul of the
                            Hawaiian Islands. That Government was never represented here. Captain
                            has applied the United States consul. Will you please send telegraph
                            instructions for his guidance.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Buchanan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>